metadata.label: Content
metadata.value: Contains: (ff. 2v-13r) Calendar with computus tables (2v, 13r). - (ff. 14r-15r) Prayer to St. James. - (16r-51r) Hours of the Virgin. - (ff. 52r-73v) Long Hours of the Cross. - (ff. 74r-93v) Hours of Eternal Wisdom. Incomplete (without beginning). - (ff. 94r-118v) Hours of the Holy Spirit. - (119r-140r) Hours of All Saints. - (ff. 141r-157r) Penitential Psalms and Litany of the Saints. - (ff. 158r-191v) Office of the Dead. - (ff. 192r-203r) Prayers. - (f. 203v) Colophon. - Empty: ff. 2r (except for crossed out owner inscription), 13v, 15v, 51v, 140v, 157v.

metadata.label: Note
value: Ownership, origin and date based on colophon: (f. 203v) "Dit getijboeck hoirt toe der eerbare vrouwen Aef van bolgerien wonende In die beverwijck. Ende heeft gescreven doer een bril broeder Gherijt van Castrinchem regulier in die beverwijck in sijn vier ende tsestichste jaer. Int jaer ons heren dusent vierhondert acht ende tnegentich. van onser vrouwen nativitas of tot die advent toe. God si geloeft. Amen". - Another ownership note (16th century) on the flyleaf (f. 1v): "Dit boeck hoort toe Cornelisge Claes Die dit boeck vint macht om goodtswil weder brengen int hem belieft".
Illumination: Painted decoration by Spierinc, dated 1499 (see f. 163r). - Leaves with painted decoration cut out between ff. 15 and 16, 73 and 74.

Binding: Post-medieval binding. - Rebound using medieval techniques (c. 1970-1990): leather over wooden boards with bevelled edges; bookblock sewn on five supports; two clasp fastenings (closing back to front). - Remnants of post-medieval binding kept in special folder under shelfmark BPL 2747 bis
Also described by BNM, MMDC and A.W. Byvanckgenootschap (database RKD, The Hague).
